 time he casts. Sure, it hasn't reset his button, but I've survived a few more seconds.<br><br>Has anyone ever tried this? Can you get far enough away? I don't want to recruit my friend to help me as this would tip my hand with this tactic. I've already killed him with my 55 bard using a similar tactic and the click-nuke boots from Cazic (and he's NOT happy about that) but bards DO run a little faster than the AAXP horse.<br><br>Any input here would be good. Also, I'm thinking I won't get too many hacks in. I'll just be jousting with him essentially. Single passes with one swing per pass. I haven't figured out how I'm going to keep him from epic'ing. I've gotta figure out how to avoid the MB. THEN I'll worry about killing him.<br><br>Thanks for the help folks.<br><br>Harlan<br>Zebuxoruk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uriggorsmortus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RiggorsMortus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 463<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/26/02 11:51:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a Wizard with MB</span><hr size=1> The horse takes time to build momentum after summoning it so I don't know if that will work too well - run3 might be a better shot <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uriggorsmortus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RiggorsMortus</A> at: 6/26/02 11:51:19 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unevroneq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NevronEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 311<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/26/02 4:20:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a Wizard with MB</span><hr size=1> You have Epic or Two handed AA bash? You might want to stare him into his eyes as you beat on him and try and time DA right as he tries to land Manaburn. It takes 6 sec with Casting time reduction items to cast Manaburn, So you still have a large margin of time, especially if you have epic or Twohanded AA skill. Thx bash.<br><br>If you on top of that have a 30%+ haste item he is just toast. Bash and Haste = dead wizard if he stands still and tries to cast MB without moving.<br><br>If you win it using psyke you won already <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p>Nevron Justicebringer<br>Knight of Tunare<br>Wolves of Retribution<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=206650>My l337 Gear</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utebin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tebin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/26/02 11:17:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a Wizard with MB</span><hr size=1> Something to try out: a wizard once told me that after you have hit the hotkey for manaburn its all or nothing, no ducking out. Like the hotkey stays darkened out. I have yet to test this but it makes sense. The hotkey prolly just triggers the effect, and does not wait to see if you land or not.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uharlan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Harlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/27/02 4:24:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a Wizard with MB</span><hr size=1> Well, I've dueled this particular wizard often enought to know that bashing is not reliable enough to be counted on. Pehaps if I had a +5% (+20%) bash item I might count on it. Vs. a 60 wizard (nevermind a melee class) I only land bash about 60% of the time. The way I won our duels in the past was to heal myself faster than he could hurt me. With critical nukes and his DD3 focus item this is tougher (though my Heal3 mask helps balance things a bit).<br><br>I have a 41% haste item and would pull up valor of Marr. That's still 5 seconds between bash attempts. Not enough time to try and land 2 per MB (given reaction times, etc.). Even at 2 bash attempts per cast I'd still have a 1/8 chance of missing him. Besides, he's not a fool. As soon as I interrupt him again he starts casting again. I would only get one bash vs. the second cast.<br><br>MB is natrually a 6 second cast time spell. Summoned or innate focus items to speed up casting will shorten that.<br><br>MB can be interrupted by ducking. Once interrupted the timer will reset and the wizard can cast again at will.<br><br>Has <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> anyone</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> here beaten a wizard with manaburn in a straight up duel? I'll have my horse soon. I've been telling him I won't duel him 'til I have a class-only AAXP skill to balance out his. I can't hold him off for too much longer.<br><br>Thanks again for the input.<br><br>Harlan<br>Zebuxoruk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utebin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tebin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/27/02 11:34:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I did</span><hr size=1> I beat a 60 wiz with MB and I am only 56, he waited till the last moment to try to MB since I guess he did not want to stand still for 6 seconds, anyway by the time he tried to MB me he was low enough on health that I killed him before he got it off. This is the same guy that told me ducking would not work. So maybe he is stupid, or wanted me to think I would be safe with DA. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uharlan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Harlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 246<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/28/02 7:47:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I did</span><hr size=1> Haha,<br><br>Well, score one for the good guys. But any wizard with MB that doesn't open with it is a fool imo. No reason to nuke a while so I can heal then MB me for less than my total HPs.<br><br>Harlan<br>Zebuxoruk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uennder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennder</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/29/02 10:08:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I did</span><hr size=1> Charge him and do a round of combat and a bash.  If you do not see interrupted use DA.  If its manaburn you just avoided it.   <p><a href =http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=210569>Fraustkilicus, Halfling Paladin</a> </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uennder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennder</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/29/02 2:18:40 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unevroneq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NevronEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 319<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/29/02 10:26:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I did</span><hr size=1> Santification does *NOT* Stop Manaburn, So don't do that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!