or=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uharlan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Harlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/1/02 12:24:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I did</span><hr size=1> A full-mana wizard doesn't scare me in the least. I haven't lost to a nuker since I was dueling 'red' /con folks (which don't exist to me any more). Just ducking doesn't prevent him trying MB again. He's got to successfully get the cast done and bounce off my DA. I'm unconvinced that I can time DA to coincide with MB landing without giving him ample opportunity to duck (0.25 seconds = ample opportunity).<br><br>I'm looking for a strategy to employ that will give me a fighting chance of preventing/surviving manaburn that doesn't rely upon timing a DA.<br><br>Harlan<br>Zebuxoruk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umoseby0.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moseby0</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/moseby/be_rickersr_hp.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/1/02 2:21:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I did</span><hr size=1> Tree's and natural obsticles are you friend. From what iv heard if he doesnt have los on you its wasted and wont hit <p>Moseby.Crusader-Luclin</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uharlan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Harlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 251<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/1/02 7:59:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I did</span><hr size=1> The LoS thing is true enough that it won't land. I don't know if it'll burn his MB (I know being OOR does not). However, most trees are world objects and not part of the 3-D map. Only objects in the 3-D model of the zone can prevent LoS. For instance, in PoG you can cast right through every tree and wall in the zone. Only the hills block line of sight.<br><br>Harlan <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uharlan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Harlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/1/02 7:59:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uramzabehoulve.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ramza Behoulve</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 183<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/2/02 12:20:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I did</span><hr size=1> Going out of LoS after the spell has been casted will "use" Manaburn and Wizard will have to wait 2h again and be oom as well. That's what casters are complaining about on my server.<br><br>They duck anytime we aren't in melee ayway now.<br><br>However, i bet in next patch that will be fixed and no mana will be used.  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31859">Sir Ra(h)mza Behoulve</a> <BR>Crusader of Karana<BR><a href="http://www.tidesofwrath.com">Tides of Wrath</a> <BR>Sullon Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ughirador.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghirador</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/2/02 1:14:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I did</span><hr size=1> <br> sorry if this sounds like a dumb question.  but does manaburn spell effects look distinct from any other spell?<br><br>also when people are talking about healing faster than the wizard can nuke, what spell are you using?  gheal, sheal, valor, daring, helm?   i can't seem to find a successful combination.  either i spend too much time rushing the wizard in which case not enough time healing and i'm dead.  its seems like in a mana contest paladins are at a severe disavantage.<br><br>isn't a typical lvl 60 wizard damage output like 6k for pvp? 11k for pve?<br><br>in which case the puzzle is doing 1500hps of damage to him before he does 6k to us.  i dunno, whats the going hps for a 60 wizard nowadays.  <br><br>Ghirador <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umalrek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malrek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/3/02 1:56:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I did</span><hr size=1> CC is our main heal.. I suppose if your really trying to get fast fast hp, you would CC first, then sup until cC wore off.. should be full health by then anyways.  <p>Reborn Knight of Vallon Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uharlan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Harlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 252<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/3/02 2:37:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I did</span><hr size=1> Manaburn is not like the necro lifeburn. It's not based on the total HPs of the caster. It's based on his mana at cast time. If I had raid buffs on (group aego, stam, focus, brells) I tip the scales at 5700-ish HPs. Even a poorly-equipped wizard at full mana will still MB for more than that on a bad hit (it's random in damage to an extent) nevermind if he crits.<br><br>Basically, if the wizard is FoM you cannot let MB land or you'ree dead - no matter what.<br><br>As for out-healing a wizard, CC and sup heal are the combination I use. Remember, I've got 3-4k HPs to go through before I drop dead. And in resist raid gear the only really effective spell a wizard can nuke with is icy spear of soloist. Things like Eldrick's Rendering, sunstrike, etc. will partial for too little to be of any threat. The nice thing (for us) abotu icy spear is that it has a few seconds recast time. Most wizards will rotate icy spear and lure of ice. I can easily out-heal that combo. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=155719&resize=true">Harlan</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wulfherehausakliufr>Wulfhere Hausakliufr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 961<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/3/02 10:43:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> try for haste?</span><hr size=1> Ah dunnae think there be a single viable tactic Harlan. That be why manaburn sucks arse reet now.<br><br>Yer options be ter kite/joust on Holy Steed, using tha terrain ter stop line o sight or fight.<br><br>Ifn yer gonna stand and fight then ya must interrupt his casting pure and simple. To interrupt yer gonna have ter rely on bash, which has aboot a 50% hit rate, melee and stuns.<br><br>So maself would do this. Get a 41% haste item. Get a 40% spell haste item or cast Valor of Marr for 25%. This will get ya ter between 66 and 81% haste on yer bash attacks. That should get yer bash rate down ter 6 seconds so ya might get a bash attempt on e'er spell cast.<br><br>Get a Journeyman's Walking stick or other weapon that procs tashan or malaise or some magic resist debuffer. Yer first job be ter give yerself a chance to stun.<br><br>Once ya have landed tashan, then switch to yer best 1h weapon and start chain casting stuns. Ah would use all o Cease, Desist, Stun, Force and QWoT. With QWoT and Force havin tha best chance to land against high resists, but ter slow ter cast unless ya land Stun first most likely.<br><br>Ifn ya cannae use a magic debuff weapon, then open up with QWoT. Ifn that lands cycle stuns and swing hard. Use bash in case any stun be resisted and cast DA at tha last second should manaburn come close ter resolving.<br><br>Allow any spell but manaburn ter go by. Save bash for mana burn.<br><br>Tha o'er 3 spells ter have memorized be Divine Aura, Superior Healing and Celestial Cleansing o course.<br><br>Trying ter keel a master wizard with Barrier of Force, while not letting them cast a single spell tho? Ah dunnae think it be possible and one spell will keel ya. Yer normal attacks willnae interrupt until tha barriers is beaten down and ya cannae spare time ter dispell tha wizard, unless ya land a Force or QWoT.<br><br>Might as well use Sanctification on any Solist comin yer way ter. Ya dunnae want ter get down on yer health thru normal spell attacks and he may use Shock o Lightning ter interrupt and toy with ya in o'er confidence. Sanctify early and pressure him.<br> <p>Wulfhere Hausakliufr<BR>Hammer o Brell, Rallos Zek</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wulfherehausakliufr>Wulfhere Hausakliufr</A> at: 7/3/02 10:47:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirtransill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Transill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/7/02 9:54:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a Wizard with MB</span><hr size=1> Well for one, if you dont have high MR then he'll just root you and then its no interrupting from there, two dueling and beating a wizzy with MB is pure luck <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ..Try dueling him near water, when he starts casting MB wait a few seconds and jump in the water, the nuke will go off but you wont take any damage if hes on land and your under water..t